metadata.name: Matter Waves #213
metadata.description:
If light, which is generally a wave, can also sometimes be a particle - then can matter also be a wave? Louis De Broglie suggested this idea, which is supported by performing a double slit experiment with matter particles and producing an interference pattern that indicates wave behaviour. Performing the experiment with one particle at a time also produces an interference pattern, implying the particles create interference with themselves. One way this could be possible is if the particle travels infinite potential paths simultaneously, super positioning itself in many places at once. If one electron can be in infinite places at once, is it possible that all electrons are that same one? More than thinking everything is connected, can we go one further and think that everything is the same thing? 

'Matter Waves' super positions connections between constellated nodes, spreading them out through space in multiple ways - an aesthetic exploration of these ideas. 

's' to save large file
'1' to watch it load slowly 
'2' to watch it load super slowly

Fully live code in p5js

www.amygoodchild.com
@amygoodchild

metadata.name: Kaibō #224
metadata.description:
What would happen if we took the natural forms that surround us and dissected them into composable shapes? 

Taking the organic world of Yashinoki, Kiabō dissects organic forms into composable elements, then reforms them into precise geometric arrangements. These shapes give way to random, organic growth the closer we look at them. 


Controls in live mode:
- Press [s] to save a png

metadata.name: codeTurning 2: push&POPing #82
metadata.description:
The codeTurning project aims to reflect my journey from traditional tools to code, in which any day I learn a new skill.
Join me towards something new for me. Something different from the previous.
Sometimes we will stand on the shoulders of giants.
 
Let's explore and see how far we get.
 
Lesson 2: push&POPing
 
With the sole initial aim of exploring push() and pop(), this stop along the way allows us to delve into the beautiful whimsy of basic colored geometric shapes. I'm having fun.

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #483
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

metadata.name: CR Art Sessions //2 #158
metadata.description:
Grayscale, Hold the Line, and Mondrian walk into a bar. The bartender looks up and says, "What is this, some kind of art project?"

Grayscale responds, "No, we're just here for a drink."

Hold the Line adds, "But we can definitely add some color to the place if you want."

Mondrian chimes in, "I prefer to keep things simple and stick to the basics."

The bartender shakes his head and says, "I'll be the judge of that. What can I get you all?"

Grayscale orders a Guinness, Hold the Line asks for a gin and tonic, and Mondrian asks for a glass of white wine.

The bartender serves up the drinks and says, "That will be $15.50, please."

Grayscale pulls out a twenty-dollar bill and hands it to the bartender, saying, "Keep the change."

The bartender thanks him and says, "Thanks, Grayscale. You always know how to liven up the place."

Hold the Line raises his glass and says, "Cheers to that!"

Mondrian nods and clinks glasses with the others, and the three of them enjoy their drinks and the rest of their evening at the bar.

-----

Press "e" to save a png (3240*4500 or 4500*3240 px) while in live mode.

-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr (2022)

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: Anarchy #176
metadata.description:
"Anarchy" aims to pay tribute to the Impressionist masters and explore the interplay between randomness and control. My goal was to capture the bold use of color and the fleeting nature of light and movement that is so characteristic of the Abstract Impressionist style. 

This piece uses a total of 12 color palettes, each one inspired by a different Impressionist painter. Some artists have two palette variations, while others only have one.

I wanted to create something that was unique and that would reflect my own visual emotions while also paying homage to the artists that inspire me. "Anarchy" is part of my exploration of the relationship between randomness and intention, and a celebration of the enduring legacy of the Impressionist masters.

Made by wandurz using p5.js 
January 2023

metadata.name: Influence no.1: Circular Expansion #87
metadata.description:
"Circular Expansion" is an abstract artwork focusing on the composition and connection of elements.
This is the first artwork from the "Influence" series. Similar to my emphasis on the importance of connections between small elements and larger elements in previous artworks, this series tries to show the connection and influence of elements on each other in a different and newer way by combining different algorithms and using multiple color palettes.
Various sizes and densities and 12 color palettes have been used.
--------
- Add &density=2-5 to the live view URL to render the image at higher resolution (Higher resolutions require more RAM space).

- Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.
